<collectingRegion box="[858,973,556,580]" country="Colombia" name="Antioquia" pageId="57">Antioquia</collectingRegion>
, the area where this species is currently known.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="57" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="57.[684,1213,226,1142]" pageId="57">
COMMENTS: The 
<typeStatus box="[903,950,623,647]" pageId="57">type</typeStatus>
specimen is not in very good condition. The apical margins of the wings are strongly notched and the setae are plastered against the integument, including the white fasciae on the apical margins of the terga and sterna. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gonzalez &amp; Griswold &amp; Engel" authorityYear="2018" box="[684,852,788,812]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paisa">
<emphasis box="[684,852,788,812]" italics="true" pageId="57">Megachile paisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is exceptionally similar morphologically to 
<taxonomicName box="[812,944,821,845]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="durantae">
<emphasis box="[812,944,821,845]" italics="true" pageId="57">M. durantae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differing in the color of the wings and body pubescence. Both species are known only from the female 
<typeStatus box="[998,1045,887,911]" pageId="57">type</typeStatus>
and they could be conspecifics. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gonzalez &amp; Griswold &amp; Engel" authorityYear="2018" box="[992,1092,921,944]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paisa">
<emphasis box="[992,1092,921,944]" italics="true" pageId="57">M. paisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[914,1026,953,977]" name="Colombia" pageId="57">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, on the eastern slope of the Cordillera Occidental. Thus, it is on the other side of the Andes, more than 
<quantity box="[1118,1213,1019,1043]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="57" unit="km" value="2000.0">2000 km</quantity>
distant from the 
<typeStatus box="[874,921,1053,1077]" pageId="57">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName box="[1046,1181,1052,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="durantae">
<emphasis box="[1046,1181,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="57">M. durantae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingRegion box="[684,794,1085,1109]" country="Brazil" name="Rondonia" pageId="57">Rondônia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[805,871,1085,1109]" name="Brazil" pageId="57">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, localities that represent rather different habitats.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
